---
// Standalone page — self-contained styles and scripts, no global.css.
// Louisiana v. Callais — SCOTUS strikes down Louisiana's congressional map
// as an unconstitutional racial gerrymander. 6-3, Alito for the majority.
// Decided April 29, 2026.
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Louisiana v. Callais: Race Out. 6-3. | Bearing Freedom</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="The Supreme Court struck down Louisiana's congressional map on April 29, 2026, ruling 6-3 that the state's second majority-Black district was an unconstitutional racial gerrymander. Maps, the holding, the 4 new Section 2 tests, and what this means for the colorblind constitution."
    />
    <meta
      property="og:title"
      content="Louisiana v. Callais: Race Out. 6-3. | Bearing Freedom"
    />
    <meta
      property="og:description"
      content="6-3. Alito for the majority. The 250-mile backslash from Shreveport to Baton Rouge is gone. Section 2 isn't dead — but the Court just hung four new locks on the door."
    />
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <meta property="og:url" content="https://bearingfreedom.com/callais" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <script async src="https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtag/js?id=G-Q6WRV03TTZ"
    ></script>
    <script is:inline>
      window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
      function gtag() {
        dataLayer.push(arguments);
      }
      gtag('js', new Date());
      gtag('config', 'G-Q6WRV03TTZ', {
        send_page_view: true,
        allow_google_signals: true,
        allow_ad_personalization_signals: true,
        cookie_flags: 'SameSite=None;Secure',
      });
    </script>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Archivo+Black&family=Fraunces:ital,opsz,wght@0,9..144,400;0,9..144,500;0,9..144,600;0,9..144,700;0,9..144,900;1,9..144,400&family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;700&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />

    <style is:global>
      *,
      *::before,
      *::after {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }

      :root {
        --void: #06080d;
        --bg: #0a0d16;
        --surface: #11151f;
        --panel: #161c2a;
        --panel-2: #1b2235;
        --border: #2a3145;
        --border-dim: #1d2336;
        --text: #f4f1e8;
        --text-mid: #c9c5b6;
        --text-dim: #8a8775;
        --text-faint: #5b5a4e;
        --gold: #d4a82a;
        --gold-deep: #8a6a18;
        --gold-glow: rgba(212, 168, 42, 0.18);
        --red: #c8333d;
        --red-deep: #8a1f29;
        --red-glow: rgba(200, 51, 61, 0.2);
        --green: #6b8e4e;
        --indigo: #3d4d8c;
        --parchment: #ede4cf;
        --parchment-deep: #c9bd9d;
        --display: 'Archivo Black', Impact, sans-serif;
        --serif: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
        --body: 'Inter', system-ui, sans-serif;
        --mono: 'JetBrains Mono', 'Courier New', monospace;
      }

      html {
        scroll-behavior: smooth;
        background: var(--void);
      }

      body {
        font-family: var(--body);
        background: var(--void);
        color: var(--text);
        line-height: 1.6;
        font-feature-settings: 'ss01', 'ss02', 'cv11';
        -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
        overflow-x: hidden;
      }

      ::selection {
        background: var(--gold);
        color: var(--void);
      }

      /* ============================================================
         JUDICIAL HEADER STRIP — case caption ribbon at the very top
         ============================================================ */
      .caption-ribbon {
        position: sticky;
        top: 0;
        z-index: 50;
        background: var(--void);
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-dim);
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 10px;
        letter-spacing: 0.18em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--text-dim);
      }
      .caption-ribbon-inner {
        max-width: 1280px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 10px 24px;
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 16px;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
      }
      .caption-ribbon a {
        color: var(--text-dim);
        text-decoration: none;
        transition: color 0.15s;
      }
      .caption-ribbon a:hover {
        color: var(--gold);
      }
      .caption-cite {
        color: var(--gold);
      }
      .caption-dot {
        display: inline-block;
        width: 4px;
        height: 4px;
        background: var(--gold);
        border-radius: 50%;
        margin: 0 10px;
        vertical-align: middle;
      }

      /* ============================================================
         SHARED LAYOUT
         ============================================================ */
      .wrap {
        max-width: 1280px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0 24px;
      }
      @media (min-width: 768px) {
        .wrap {
          padding: 0 48px;
        }
      }

      .section {
        padding: 80px 0;
        position: relative;
      }
      @media (min-width: 768px) {
        .section {
          padding: 120px 0;
        }
      }

      .section-num {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 11px;
        letter-spacing: 0.3em;
        color: var(--gold);
        text-transform: uppercase;
        margin-bottom: 18px;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 12px;
      }
      .section-num::after {
        content: '';
        flex: 1;
        height: 1px;
        background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--gold-glow), transparent);
        max-width: 120px;
      }
      .section-title {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-weight: 900;
        font-size: clamp(36px, 6vw, 68px);
        line-height: 0.95;
        letter-spacing: -0.02em;
        color: var(--text);
        margin-bottom: 24px;
        font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 144;
      }
      .section-title em {
        font-style: italic;
        color: var(--gold);
        font-weight: 500;
      }
      .section-lede {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-size: 22px;
        line-height: 1.5;
        color: var(--text-mid);
        max-width: 720px;
        margin-bottom: 56px;
        font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 32;
      }
      @media (min-width: 768px) {
        .section-lede {
          font-size: 26px;
        }
      }

      /* ============================================================
         HERO
         ============================================================ */
      .hero {
        min-height: calc(100vh - 40px);
        position: relative;
        background:
          radial-gradient(
            ellipse at top right,
            rgba(212, 168, 42, 0.12),
            transparent 50%
          ),
          radial-gradient(
            ellipse at bottom left,
            rgba(200, 51, 61, 0.08),
            transparent 50%
          ),
          var(--void);
        overflow: hidden;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
      }

      /* Marble/parchment texture overlay */
      .hero::before {
        content: '';
        position: absolute;
        inset: 0;
        background-image:
          repeating-linear-gradient(
            0deg,
            rgba(244, 241, 232, 0.015) 0,
            rgba(244, 241, 232, 0.015) 1px,
            transparent 1px,
            transparent 3px
          ),
          repeating-linear-gradient(
            90deg,
            rgba(244, 241, 232, 0.015) 0,
            rgba(244, 241, 232, 0.015) 1px,
            transparent 1px,
            transparent 3px
          );
        pointer-events: none;
        mix-blend-mode: overlay;
      }

      /* Faint Roman numeral background mark */
      .hero::after {
        content: 'VI · III';
        position: absolute;
        right: -2vw;
        bottom: -8vw;
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-size: clamp(200px, 40vw, 600px);
        font-weight: 900;
        color: rgba(212, 168, 42, 0.04);
        line-height: 1;
        pointer-events: none;
        font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 144;
        letter-spacing: -0.04em;
      }

      .hero-inner {
        position: relative;
        z-index: 2;
        width: 100%;
        padding: 80px 0 60px;
      }

      .hero-eyebrow {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 12px;
        letter-spacing: 0.3em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--gold);
        margin-bottom: 28px;
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 14px;
      }
      .hero-eyebrow::before {
        content: '';
        width: 32px;
        height: 1px;
        background: var(--gold);
      }

      .hero-cite {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-style: italic;
        font-weight: 500;
        font-size: clamp(20px, 2.4vw, 28px);
        color: var(--text-mid);
        margin-bottom: 16px;
        font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 48;
      }
      .hero-cite .v {
        color: var(--text-faint);
        margin: 0 8px;
        font-style: normal;
      }

      .hero-title {
        font-family: var(--display);
        font-size: clamp(64px, 14vw, 220px);
        line-height: 0.85;
        letter-spacing: -0.04em;
        color: var(--text);
        margin: 18px 0 0;
        text-transform: uppercase;
      }
      .hero-title .race {
        display: block;
      }
      .hero-title .out {
        display: block;
        color: var(--gold);
        position: relative;
      }
      .hero-title .out::after {
        content: '';
        position: absolute;
        left: -2%;
        top: 48%;
        width: 104%;
        height: 14%;
        background: var(--red);
        transform: rotate(-3deg);
        z-index: -1;
        opacity: 0.85;
        box-shadow: 0 0 40px var(--red-glow);
      }

      .hero-meta {
        margin-top: 56px;
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
        gap: 0;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      }
      @media (min-width: 768px) {
        .hero-meta {
          grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
        }
      }
      .hero-stat {
        padding: 24px 28px;
        border-right: 1px solid var(--border);
      }
      .hero-stat:last-child {
        border-right: none;
      }
      .hero-stat:nth-child(2n) {
        border-right: none;
      }
      @media (min-width: 768px) {
        .hero-stat:nth-child(2n) {
          border-right: 1px solid var(--border);
        }
        .hero-stat:last-child {
          border-right: none;
        }
      }
      .hero-stat-label {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 10px;
        letter-spacing: 0.25em;
        color: var(--text-faint);
        text-transform: uppercase;
        margin-bottom: 12px;
      }
      .hero-stat-value {
        font-family: var(--display);
        font-size: 28px;
        line-height: 1.05;
        color: var(--text);
        letter-spacing: -0.01em;
      }
      .hero-stat-value.gold {
        color: var(--gold);
      }
      .hero-stat-sub {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 11px;
        color: var(--text-dim);
        margin-top: 6px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      }

      .hero-stamp {
        position: absolute;
        top: 110px;
        right: 24px;
        width: 180px;
        height: 180px;
        border: 3px solid var(--red);
        border-radius: 50%;
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        transform: rotate(-12deg);
        opacity: 0.9;
        font-family: var(--display);
        color: var(--red);
        box-shadow:
          inset 0 0 0 6px var(--void),
          inset 0 0 0 7px var(--red);
        text-align: center;
      }
      .hero-stamp::before,
      .hero-stamp::after {
        content: '';
        position: absolute;
        left: 12%;
        right: 12%;
        height: 1.5px;
        background: var(--red);
      }
      .hero-stamp::before {
        top: 26%;
      }
      .hero-stamp::after {
        bottom: 26%;
      }
      .hero-stamp-main {
        font-size: 26px;
        letter-spacing: 0.06em;
        line-height: 1;
      }
      .hero-stamp-sub {
        font-size: 9px;
        letter-spacing: 0.18em;
        margin-top: 4px;
        font-family: var(--mono);
      }
      @media (max-width: 900px) {
        .hero-stamp {
          position: static;
          margin: 40px auto 0;
          transform: rotate(-6deg);
        }
      }

      /* ============================================================
         OPINION QUOTE BLOCK
         ============================================================ */
      .opinion {
        background: var(--bg);
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border-dim);
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-dim);
        padding: 100px 0;
        position: relative;
      }
      .opinion::before {
        content: '';
        position: absolute;
        top: 0;
        left: 50%;
        transform: translateX(-50%);
        width: 1px;
        height: 60px;
        background: var(--gold);
        opacity: 0.4;
      }
      .opinion-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        gap: 40px;
      }
      @media (min-width: 900px) {
        .opinion-grid {
          grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr;
          gap: 80px;
        }
      }
      .opinion-byline {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 11px;
        letter-spacing: 0.2em;
        color: var(--text-dim);
        text-transform: uppercase;
        line-height: 1.8;
      }
      .opinion-byline strong {
        color: var(--gold);
        display: block;
        font-size: 14px;
        font-family: var(--display);
        font-weight: normal;
        letter-spacing: 0.04em;
        margin-bottom: 6px;
      }
      .opinion-quote {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 48px);
        line-height: 1.18;
        font-weight: 500;
        color: var(--text);
        text-indent: -0.4em;
        font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 144;
        letter-spacing: -0.01em;
      }
      .opinion-quote em {
        font-style: italic;
        color: var(--gold);
      }
      .opinion-quote::before {
        content: '"';
        font-size: 1.4em;
        color: var(--gold);
        line-height: 0;
        vertical-align: -0.2em;
        margin-right: 0.05em;
      }
      .opinion-quote::after {
        content: '"';
        color: var(--gold);
        margin-left: 0.05em;
      }

      /* ============================================================
         MAPS
         ============================================================ */
      .maps-section {
        background: var(--void);
      }
      .map-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        gap: 32px;
      }
      @media (min-width: 1100px) {
        .map-grid {
          grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
        }
      }

      .map-card {
        background: var(--surface);
        border: 1px solid var(--border-dim);
        position: relative;
        overflow: hidden;
        transition:
          border-color 0.3s,
          transform 0.3s;
      }
      .map-card:hover {
        border-color: var(--border);
      }
      .map-card.struck {
        border-color: var(--red-deep);
      }

      .map-tag {
        position: absolute;
        top: 16px;
        right: 16px;
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 10px;
        letter-spacing: 0.18em;
        padding: 6px 10px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        background: var(--panel);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        color: var(--text-dim);
        z-index: 3;
      }
      .map-tag.live {
        color: var(--green);
        border-color: var(--green);
      }
      .map-tag.struck {
        color: var(--red);
        border-color: var(--red);
      }
      .map-tag.tbd {
        color: var(--gold);
        border-color: var(--gold);
      }

      .map-header {
        padding: 28px 28px 20px;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-dim);
      }
      .map-eyebrow {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 10px;
        letter-spacing: 0.25em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--text-faint);
        margin-bottom: 8px;
      }
      .map-title {
        font-family: var(--display);
        font-size: 22px;
        line-height: 1.05;
        margin-bottom: 8px;
        color: var(--text);
        letter-spacing: -0.01em;
      }
      .map-subtitle {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-size: 14px;
        color: var(--text-dim);
        font-style: italic;
        font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 14;
      }

      .map-svg-wrap {
        position: relative;
        padding: 16px;
        background: var(--surface);
      }
      /* Real-map exhibit frame: parchment-toned well behind a CC-licensed map */
      .map-frame {
        position: relative;
        background: #faf6ec;
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        box-shadow:
          inset 0 0 0 6px #faf6ec,
          inset 0 0 0 7px #d8cfb4,
          0 8px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4);
        padding: 0;
        overflow: hidden;
      }
      .map-frame img {
        display: block;
        width: 100%;
        height: auto;
      }
      .map-card.struck .map-frame::after {
        content: 'VOID';
        position: absolute;
        top: 50%;
        left: 50%;
        transform: translate(-50%, -50%) rotate(-22deg);
        font-family: var(--display);
        font-size: clamp(72px, 18vw, 132px);
        color: var(--red);
        opacity: 0.42;
        letter-spacing: 0.12em;
        pointer-events: none;
        z-index: 2;
        text-shadow: 0 2px 0 rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
        white-space: nowrap;
      }
      .map-card.struck .map-frame {
        box-shadow:
          inset 0 0 0 6px #faf6ec,
          inset 0 0 0 7px var(--red),
          0 8px 24px rgba(200, 51, 61, 0.18);
      }
      .map-attrib {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 9px;
        letter-spacing: 0.16em;
        color: var(--text-faint);
        text-transform: uppercase;
        padding: 8px 16px 0;
        text-align: right;
      }
      .map-attrib a {
        color: var(--text-dim);
        text-decoration: none;
      }
      .map-attrib a:hover {
        color: var(--gold);
      }
      .map-svg-wrap svg {
        width: 100%;
        height: auto;
        display: block;
      }

      /* SVG district fills */
      .d-fill {
        transition: fill 0.3s;
      }
      .d-1 {
        fill: #2c5078;
      } /* New Orleans suburbs/coast */
      .d-2 {
        fill: #8a3434;
      } /* New Orleans urban (maj-Black) */
      .d-3 {
        fill: #5a6e3a;
      } /* SW (Lafayette/Lake Charles) */
      .d-4 {
        fill: #6b4789;
      } /* NW (Shreveport) */
      .d-5 {
        fill: #b5832a;
      } /* North/East */
      .d-6 {
        fill: #2d6f64;
      } /* Capital region (Baton Rouge) */
      .d-6-snake {
        fill: #a82a36;
      } /* Struck-down CD-6 backslash */

      .d-stroke {
        stroke: var(--void);
        stroke-width: 1.4;
        stroke-linejoin: round;
      }
      .la-outline {
        fill: none;
        stroke: var(--text);
        stroke-width: 2;
      }

      .d-label {
        font-family: var(--display);
        font-size: 14px;
        fill: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.92);
        text-anchor: middle;
        pointer-events: none;
        letter-spacing: 0.04em;
      }
      .city-dot {
        fill: var(--parchment);
        stroke: var(--void);
        stroke-width: 1;
      }
      .city-label {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 9px;
        fill: var(--text-mid);
        letter-spacing: 0.06em;
      }
      .legend-tag {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 9px;
        fill: var(--text-dim);
        letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      }

      .map-stats {
        padding: 20px 28px;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border-dim);
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
        gap: 12px;
      }
      .map-stat-label {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 9px;
        letter-spacing: 0.18em;
        color: var(--text-faint);
        text-transform: uppercase;
        margin-bottom: 4px;
      }
      .map-stat-value {
        font-family: var(--display);
        font-size: 20px;
        color: var(--text);
        line-height: 1;
      }
      .map-card.struck .map-stat-value.flag {
        color: var(--red);
      }
      .map-stat-value.gold {
        color: var(--gold);
      }

      .map-foot {
        padding: 18px 28px 24px;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border-dim);
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-size: 14px;
        color: var(--text-mid);
        line-height: 1.55;
        font-style: italic;
      }
      .map-foot strong {
        font-style: normal;
        color: var(--text);
        font-weight: 600;
      }

      /* ============================================================
         CD-6 ANATOMY (the snake) — large featured detail
         ============================================================ */
      .anatomy {
        background: var(--bg);
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border-dim);
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-dim);
      }
      .anatomy-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        gap: 48px;
        align-items: center;
      }
      @media (min-width: 1000px) {
        .anatomy-grid {
          grid-template-columns: 1.2fr 1fr;
          gap: 80px;
        }
      }
      .anatomy-svg {
        position: relative;
      }
      .anatomy-svg .map-frame {
        box-shadow:
          inset 0 0 0 8px #faf6ec,
          inset 0 0 0 9px var(--red),
          0 12px 32px rgba(200, 51, 61, 0.18);
      }
      .anatomy-svg img {
        display: block;
        width: 100%;
        height: auto;
      }
      .anatomy-call {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 10px;
        letter-spacing: 0.2em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--gold);
      }
      .anatomy h2 {
        font-family: var(--display);
        font-size: clamp(36px, 5vw, 64px);
        line-height: 0.95;
        margin: 12px 0 24px;
        letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      }
      .anatomy h2 span {
        color: var(--red);
      }
      .anatomy p {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-size: 19px;
        line-height: 1.55;
        color: var(--text-mid);
        margin-bottom: 18px;
        font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 19;
      }
      .anatomy ul {
        list-style: none;
        margin-top: 32px;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border-dim);
      }
      .anatomy li {
        padding: 18px 0;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-dim);
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 90px 1fr;
        gap: 24px;
        align-items: baseline;
      }
      .anatomy li .num {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 11px;
        letter-spacing: 0.18em;
        color: var(--gold);
        text-transform: uppercase;
      }
      .anatomy li .body {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-size: 17px;
        color: var(--text);
        line-height: 1.5;
      }
      .anatomy li .body strong {
        color: var(--gold);
        font-weight: 700;
      }

      /* ============================================================
         FOUR NEW TESTS — section 2 considerations
         ============================================================ */
      .tests {
        background: var(--void);
      }
      .tests-intro {
        max-width: 760px;
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-size: 20px;
        line-height: 1.55;
        color: var(--text-mid);
        margin-bottom: 56px;
      }
      .tests-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        gap: 1px;
        background: var(--border-dim);
        border: 1px solid var(--border-dim);
      }
      @media (min-width: 700px) {
        .tests-grid {
          grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
        }
      }
      .test-card {
        background: var(--surface);
        padding: 36px 32px;
        position: relative;
        transition: background 0.3s;
      }
      .test-card:hover {
        background: var(--panel);
      }
      .test-num {
        font-family: var(--display);
        font-size: 80px;
        line-height: 1;
        color: var(--gold);
        opacity: 0.15;
        position: absolute;
        top: 18px;
        right: 28px;
        font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
      }
      .test-tag {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 10px;
        letter-spacing: 0.22em;
        color: var(--gold);
        text-transform: uppercase;
        margin-bottom: 16px;
      }
      .test-title {
        font-family: var(--display);
        font-size: 22px;
        line-height: 1.15;
        color: var(--text);
        margin-bottom: 14px;
        letter-spacing: -0.01em;
      }
      .test-body {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-size: 16px;
        line-height: 1.6;
        color: var(--text-mid);
      }

      /* ============================================================
         DISSENT BLOCK
         ============================================================ */
      .dissent {
        background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--void), var(--bg)), var(--bg);
        position: relative;
      }
      .dissent-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        gap: 40px;
      }
      @media (min-width: 900px) {
        .dissent-grid {
          grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr;
          gap: 80px;
        }
      }
      .dissent-byline {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 11px;
        letter-spacing: 0.2em;
        color: var(--text-dim);
        text-transform: uppercase;
        line-height: 1.8;
      }
      .dissent-byline strong {
        color: var(--red);
        font-family: var(--display);
        font-weight: normal;
        font-size: 14px;
        letter-spacing: 0.04em;
        display: block;
        margin-bottom: 6px;
      }
      .dissent-quote {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-size: clamp(26px, 3.6vw, 44px);
        line-height: 1.22;
        color: var(--text);
        font-style: italic;
        font-weight: 400;
        font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 144;
        letter-spacing: -0.005em;
      }
      .dissent-quote em {
        font-style: normal;
        color: var(--red);
        font-weight: 600;
      }
      .dissent-quote::before {
        content: '"';
        color: var(--red);
        font-size: 1.3em;
        line-height: 0;
        vertical-align: -0.2em;
        margin-right: 0.05em;
      }

      /* ============================================================
         2A ANGLE — Why this matters for gun rights
         ============================================================ */
      .angle {
        background: var(--void);
        position: relative;
        overflow: hidden;
      }
      .angle::before {
        content: '';
        position: absolute;
        top: 0;
        right: 0;
        width: 50%;
        height: 100%;
        background: radial-gradient(
          ellipse at right,
          rgba(212, 168, 42, 0.06),
          transparent 60%
        );
        pointer-events: none;
      }

      .angle-stamp {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 10px;
        letter-spacing: 0.3em;
        color: var(--gold);
        text-transform: uppercase;
        margin-bottom: 18px;
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 10px;
      }
      .angle-stamp::before {
        content: '';
        width: 20px;
        height: 1px;
        background: var(--gold);
      }
      .angle-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        gap: 56px;
      }
      @media (min-width: 1000px) {
        .angle-grid {
          grid-template-columns: 1.1fr 1fr;
        }
      }
      .angle-body p {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-size: 19px;
        line-height: 1.6;
        color: var(--text-mid);
        margin-bottom: 22px;
        font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 19;
      }
      .angle-body p strong {
        color: var(--text);
        font-weight: 600;
      }
      .angle-body p em {
        color: var(--gold);
        font-style: italic;
      }
      .angle-pull {
        font-family: var(--display);
        font-size: clamp(28px, 3.4vw, 42px);
        line-height: 1.1;
        color: var(--text);
        margin: 36px 0;
        padding: 28px 0 28px 32px;
        border-left: 4px solid var(--gold);
        letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      }
      .angle-pull span {
        color: var(--gold);
      }

      .precedent-stack {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 14px;
      }
      .precedent {
        background: var(--surface);
        border: 1px solid var(--border-dim);
        padding: 22px 24px;
        position: relative;
        transition:
          border-color 0.3s,
          transform 0.3s;
      }
      .precedent:hover {
        border-color: var(--gold);
        transform: translateX(4px);
      }
      .precedent-cite {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-style: italic;
        font-size: 18px;
        color: var(--gold);
        margin-bottom: 8px;
        font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 24;
      }
      .precedent-year {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 10px;
        color: var(--text-faint);
        letter-spacing: 0.18em;
        position: absolute;
        top: 22px;
        right: 24px;
      }
      .precedent-line {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-size: 15px;
        color: var(--text-mid);
        line-height: 1.5;
      }

      /* ============================================================
         WHAT'S NEXT — timeline / next steps
         ============================================================ */
      .next-section {
        background: var(--bg);
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border-dim);
      }
      .next-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        gap: 16px;
      }
      @media (min-width: 800px) {
        .next-grid {
          grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
        }
      }
      .next-card {
        background: var(--surface);
        border: 1px solid var(--border-dim);
        padding: 28px;
        transition: border-color 0.3s;
      }
      .next-card:hover {
        border-color: var(--gold);
      }
      .next-when {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 10px;
        letter-spacing: 0.22em;
        color: var(--gold);
        text-transform: uppercase;
        margin-bottom: 14px;
      }
      .next-headline {
        font-family: var(--display);
        font-size: 19px;
        line-height: 1.15;
        color: var(--text);
        margin-bottom: 12px;
        letter-spacing: -0.01em;
      }
      .next-body {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-size: 15px;
        line-height: 1.55;
        color: var(--text-mid);
      }

      /* ============================================================
         RIPPLE — other states
         ============================================================ */
      .ripple {
        background: var(--void);
      }
      .ripple-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
        gap: 1px;
        background: var(--border-dim);
        border: 1px solid var(--border-dim);
      }
      @media (min-width: 700px) {
        .ripple-grid {
          grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
        }
      }
      .ripple-cell {
        background: var(--surface);
        padding: 28px 24px;
      }
      .ripple-state {
        font-family: var(--display);
        font-size: 28px;
        color: var(--gold);
        line-height: 1;
        margin-bottom: 12px;
        letter-spacing: -0.01em;
      }
      .ripple-tag {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 9px;
        letter-spacing: 0.2em;
        color: var(--text-faint);
        text-transform: uppercase;
        margin-bottom: 10px;
      }
      .ripple-body {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-size: 14px;
        color: var(--text-mid);
        line-height: 1.5;
      }

      /* ============================================================
         FOOTER — sources / case info
         ============================================================ */
      .colophon {
        background: var(--void);
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border-dim);
        padding: 60px 0 80px;
      }
      .colophon-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        gap: 40px;
      }
      @media (min-width: 700px) {
        .colophon-grid {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        }
      }
      @media (min-width: 1100px) {
        .colophon-grid {
          grid-template-columns: 1.2fr 1fr 1fr 1fr;
        }
      }
      .colophon h4 {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 10px;
        letter-spacing: 0.25em;
        color: var(--gold);
        text-transform: uppercase;
        margin-bottom: 16px;
      }
      .colophon p,
      .colophon li {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-size: 15px;
        line-height: 1.6;
        color: var(--text-mid);
      }
      .colophon ul {
        list-style: none;
      }
      .colophon li {
        padding: 8px 0;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-dim);
      }
      .colophon a {
        color: var(--text);
        text-decoration: none;
        transition: color 0.2s;
      }
      .colophon a:hover {
        color: var(--gold);
      }
      .colophon-cite {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-style: italic;
        font-size: 18px;
        color: var(--gold);
        margin-bottom: 8px;
      }
      .colophon-meta {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 10px;
        color: var(--text-faint);
        letter-spacing: 0.15em;
        margin-top: 24px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        line-height: 1.8;
      }

      /* ============================================================
         REVEAL ANIMATIONS
         ============================================================ */
      [data-reveal] {
        opacity: 0;
        transform: translateY(24px);
        transition:
          opacity 0.8s ease,
          transform 0.8s ease;
      }
      [data-reveal].visible {
        opacity: 1;
        transform: none;
      }
      [data-reveal-delay='1'] {
        transition-delay: 0.08s;
      }
      [data-reveal-delay='2'] {
        transition-delay: 0.16s;
      }
      [data-reveal-delay='3'] {
        transition-delay: 0.24s;
      }
      [data-reveal-delay='4'] {
        transition-delay: 0.32s;
      }

      @keyframes stamp-in {
        0% {
          opacity: 0;
          transform: rotate(-20deg) scale(1.4);
        }
        60% {
          opacity: 1;
          transform: rotate(-8deg) scale(0.95);
        }
        100% {
          opacity: 0.9;
          transform: rotate(-12deg) scale(1);
        }
      }
      .hero-stamp {
        animation: stamp-in 1.1s 0.4s both;
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
    <!-- ============================================================
         CASE CAPTION RIBBON
         ============================================================ -->
    <div class="caption-ribbon">
      <div class="caption-ribbon-inner">
        <span>
          <span class="caption-cite">Louisiana</span> v.
          <span class="caption-cite">Callais</span>
          <span class="caption-dot"></span>
          No. 24-109
          <span class="caption-dot"></span>
          Decided April 29, 2026
        </span>
        <a href="/extras">&larr; Back to extras</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ============================================================
         HERO
         ============================================================ -->
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="wrap hero-inner">
        <div class="hero-stamp">
          <span class="hero-stamp-main">VOID</span>
          <span class="hero-stamp-sub">RACIAL GERRYMANDER</span>
        </div>

        <div class="hero-eyebrow" data-reveal>
          Supreme Court of the United States &mdash; April Term 2026
        </div>

        <div class="hero-cite" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="1">
          <span>Louisiana</span><span class="v">v.</span><span>Callais</span>
        </div>

        <h1 class="hero-title" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="2">
          <span class="race">Race</span>
          <span class="out">Out.</span>
        </h1>

        <div class="hero-meta" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="3">
          <div class="hero-stat">
            <div class="hero-stat-label">Vote</div>
            <div class="hero-stat-value gold">6 &mdash; 3</div>
            <div class="hero-stat-sub">Ideological split</div>
          </div>
          <div class="hero-stat">
            <div class="hero-stat-label">Majority</div>
            <div class="hero-stat-value">Alito, J.</div>
            <div class="hero-stat-sub">
              Roberts &middot; Thomas &middot; Gorsuch &middot; Kavanaugh
              &middot; Barrett
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="hero-stat">
            <div class="hero-stat-label">Dissent</div>
            <div class="hero-stat-value">Kagan, J.</div>
            <div class="hero-stat-sub">Sotomayor &middot; Jackson</div>
          </div>
          <div class="hero-stat">
            <div class="hero-stat-label">Holding</div>
            <div class="hero-stat-value gold">Map struck.</div>
            <div class="hero-stat-sub">14th Amendment violation</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ============================================================
         OPINION QUOTE
         ============================================================ -->
    <section class="opinion">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="opinion-grid">
          <div class="opinion-byline" data-reveal>
            <strong>Majority &mdash; Alito, J.</strong>
            Slip op., at 24<br />
            Apr. 29, 2026
          </div>
          <blockquote class="opinion-quote" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="1">
            Allowing race to play any part in government decision-making
            represents a <em>departure from the constitutional rule</em>
            that applies in almost every other context.
          </blockquote>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ============================================================
         THE THREE MAPS
         ============================================================ -->
    <section class="section maps-section" id="maps">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="section-num" data-reveal>I &middot; The exhibits</div>
        <h2 class="section-title" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="1">
          One state. <em>Three maps.</em>
        </h2>
        <p class="section-lede" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="2">
          Louisiana redrew its congressional districts twice between 2022 and
          2024. The Court took one of those maps off the wall and pinned it to
          the bench as exhibit A in a racial-gerrymander case.
        </p>

        <div class="map-grid">
          <!-- ====== MAP 1: 2022 baseline ====== -->
          <article class="map-card" data-reveal>
            <div class="map-tag">Predecessor</div>
            <div class="map-header">
              <div class="map-eyebrow">Map I &middot; 2022 baseline</div>
              <div class="map-title">The first map</div>
              <div class="map-subtitle">
                One Black-majority district. Federal court found this violated
                Section 2 of the Voting Rights Act in <em>Robinson v. Ardoin</em
                >.
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="map-svg-wrap">
              <div class="map-frame">
                <img
                  src="/maps/la-118th-congress.svg"
                  alt="Louisiana congressional districts under the 2022 Robinson-era map (118th Congress). One majority-Black district: CD-2, the urban New Orleans corridor."
                  loading="lazy"
                />
              </div>
              <div class="map-attrib">
                Map: <a
                  href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Louisiana_Congressional_Districts,_118th_Congress.svg"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener">Wikimedia / Twotwofourtysix</a
                > &middot; CC BY-SA 4.0
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="map-stats">
              <div>
                <div class="map-stat-label">Maj-Black</div>
                <div class="map-stat-value gold">1 / 6</div>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="map-stat-label">Drawn</div>
                <div class="map-stat-value">2022</div>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="map-stat-label">Status</div>
                <div class="map-stat-value">Replaced</div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="map-foot">
              <strong>Federal Judge Shelly Dick</strong> ordered Louisiana to add
              a second Black-majority district in June 2022. The legislature's first
              map didn't comply.
            </div>
          </article>

          <!-- ====== MAP 2: SB8 (2024 — STRUCK DOWN) ====== -->
          <article class="map-card struck" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="1">
            <div class="map-tag struck">Struck down</div>
            <div class="map-header">
              <div class="map-eyebrow">Map II &middot; SB8 (Act 2)</div>
              <div class="map-title">The 250-mile backslash</div>
              <div class="map-subtitle">
                CD-6 redrawn from <em>Shreveport</em> diagonally through
                <em>Alexandria</em> and <em>Lafayette</em> to
                <em>Baton Rouge</em>. The Court called it a racial gerrymander.
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="map-svg-wrap">
              <div class="map-frame">
                <img
                  src="/maps/la-119th-congress.svg"
                  alt="Louisiana congressional districts under the SB8 map (119th Congress) — struck down April 29, 2026. Two majority-Black districts: CD-2 (urban) and CD-6, the diagonal Shreveport-to-Baton Rouge district."
                  loading="lazy"
                />
              </div>
              <div class="map-attrib">
                Map: <a
                  href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Louisiana_Congressional_Districts,_119th_Congress.svg"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener">Wikimedia / Twotwofourtysix</a
                > &middot; CC BY-SA 4.0
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="map-stats">
              <div>
                <div class="map-stat-label">Maj-Black</div>
                <div class="map-stat-value flag">2 / 6</div>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="map-stat-label">CD-6 Black VAP</div>
                <div class="map-stat-value">54%</div>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="map-stat-label">Status</div>
                <div class="map-stat-value flag">Voided</div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="map-foot">
              The legislature lifted CD-6 from <strong>23% Black VAP</strong>
              to <strong>54%</strong> in a single session.
              <strong>Cleo Fields (D)</strong> won the seat in November 2024. The
              Court ruled today that the line-drawers leaned too hard on race.
            </div>
          </article>

          <!-- ====== MAP 3: TBD ====== -->
          <article class="map-card" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="2">
            <div class="map-tag tbd">Pending</div>
            <div class="map-header">
              <div class="map-eyebrow">Map III &middot; Remand</div>
              <div class="map-title">The replacement</div>
              <div class="map-subtitle">
                Back to Louisiana to redraw &mdash; or to a federal court if the
                legislature stalls. Same problem, narrower path through the new
                Section 2 tests.
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="map-svg-wrap">
              <svg
                viewBox="0 0 360 280"
                aria-label="Louisiana redraw pending — placeholder map"
              >
                <defs>
                  <pattern
                    id="grid3"
                    width="14"
                    height="14"
                    patternUnits="userSpaceOnUse"
                  >
                    <path
                      d="M14 0 L0 0 L0 14"
                      fill="none"
                      stroke="rgba(212,168,42,0.06)"
                      stroke-width="0.5"></path>
                  </pattern>
                  <pattern
                    id="hatchgold"
                    width="8"
                    height="8"
                    patternUnits="userSpaceOnUse"
                    patternTransform="rotate(45)"
                  >
                    <line
                      x1="0"
                      y1="0"
                      x2="0"
                      y2="8"
                      stroke="rgba(212,168,42,0.35)"
                      stroke-width="1"></line>
                  </pattern>
                </defs>
                <rect width="360" height="280" fill="url(#grid3)"></rect>

                <!-- Single LA outline filled with hatch — TBD -->
                <path
                  d="
                  M30 30 L320 30 L320 200 L300 220 L260 250 L180 260 L120 240 L60 215 L30 150 Z"
                  fill="url(#hatchgold)"
                  stroke="var(--gold)"
                  stroke-width="2"
                  stroke-dasharray="4 4"></path>

                <!-- Question mark big -->
                <text
                  x="180"
                  y="160"
                  text-anchor="middle"
                  font-family="Archivo Black"
                  font-size="120"
                  fill="rgba(212,168,42,0.6)">?</text
                >

                <!-- Caption -->
                <text
                  x="180"
                  y="220"
                  text-anchor="middle"
                  font-family="JetBrains Mono"
                  font-size="10"
                  fill="var(--gold)"
                  letter-spacing="2"
                >
                  AWAITING LEGISLATIVE ACTION
                </text>
              </svg>
            </div>

            <div class="map-stats">
              <div>
                <div class="map-stat-label">Maj-Black</div>
                <div class="map-stat-value gold">TBD</div>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="map-stat-label">Deadline</div>
                <div class="map-stat-value">2026 cycle</div>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="map-stat-label">Status</div>
                <div class="map-stat-value gold">Remand</div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="map-foot">
              The legislature gets first crack. If they punt, the
              <strong>Western District of Louisiana</strong> draws the next one. Either
              way: the Section 2 path just got four locks added to it.
            </div>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ============================================================
         CD-6 ANATOMY — the snake detail
         ============================================================ -->
    <section class="section anatomy">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="anatomy-grid">
          <div class="anatomy-svg" data-reveal>
            <div class="map-frame">
              <img
                src="/maps/la-cd6-2025.svg"
                alt="Louisiana's 6th Congressional District as drawn under SB8 — outlined in red running diagonally from Caddo Parish (Shreveport) southeast through Natchitoches, Alexandria, Opelousas, to East Baton Rouge Parish."
                loading="lazy"
              />
            </div>
            <div class="map-attrib">
              Map: <a
                href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Louisiana%27s_6th_congressional_district_(since_2025).svg"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener">Wikimedia / Twotwofourtysix</a
              > &middot; CC BY-SA 4.0
            </div>
          </div>

          <div data-reveal data-reveal-delay="1">
            <div class="anatomy-call">II &middot; Anatomy of a snake</div>
            <h2>The line that <span>broke</span> the rule.</h2>
            <p>
              CD-6 used to be a Baton Rouge anchor. SB8 stretched it across
              two-thirds of the state on a single mission: hit
              <em>50 percent</em> Black VAP. The path was the giveaway.
            </p>
            <p>
              You can&apos;t draw a 250-mile diagonal through three regions and
              tell a federal court the route was about anything other than the
              racial composition of the neighborhoods you grabbed on the way.
            </p>

            <ul>
              <li>
                <span class="num">Length</span>
                <span class="body">
                  <strong>~250 miles</strong> of contiguous district running northwest
                  to southeast.
                </span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="num">Black VAP</span>
                <span class="body">
                  Lifted from <strong>23%</strong> to <strong>54%</strong>
                  in one redraw.
                </span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="num">Trace</span>
                <span class="body">
                  Hugs the Red and Mississippi rivers, threading majority-Black
                  neighborhoods through Caddo, Rapides, East Baton Rouge.
                </span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="num">Holding</span>
                <span class="body">
                  The Court found the route was &quot;explicable only by
                  reference to race.&quot;
                </span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ============================================================
         FOUR NEW SECTION 2 TESTS
         ============================================================ -->
    <section class="section tests">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="section-num" data-reveal>III &middot; The new locks</div>
        <h2 class="section-title" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="1">
          Four reasons the old <em>Gingles</em> test no longer fits.
        </h2>
        <p class="tests-intro" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="2">
          The Court didn&apos;t kill Section 2. It said the 1986 Gingles
          framework was built for a country that doesn&apos;t exist anymore, and
          added four new considerations every plaintiff has to clear. Kagan
          calls this killing the statute slowly. Either way, the door is much
          smaller than it was yesterday.
        </p>

        <div class="tests-grid">
          <div class="test-card" data-reveal>
            <div class="test-num">01</div>
            <div class="test-tag">Consideration I</div>
            <h3 class="test-title">No more entrenched Jim Crow.</h3>
            <p class="test-body">
              The Southern political machinery that Section 2 was written to
              break is gone. The majority says courts can no longer presume the
              same baseline of state hostility that justified race-conscious
              remedies in 1965 or 1986.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="test-card" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="1">
            <div class="test-num">02</div>
            <div class="test-tag">Consideration II</div>
            <h3 class="test-title">Race tracks party.</h3>
            <p class="test-body">
              In a polarized two-party system, race and partisan affiliation
              correlate sharply. A &quot;racially polarized vote&quot; under
              Gingles is now functionally indistinguishable from a partisan vote
              &mdash; which the Court has already pulled out of federal
              jurisdiction.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="test-card" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="2">
            <div class="test-num">03</div>
            <div class="test-tag">Consideration III</div>
            <h3 class="test-title">Rucho closed the partisan door.</h3>
            <p class="test-body">
              <em>Rucho v. Common Cause</em> (2019) made partisan gerrymandering nonjusticiable
              in federal court. Using race as a proxy for party to get the same remedy
              through the side door of Section 2 is, the majority holds, an end-run
              around Rucho.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="test-card" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="3">
            <div class="test-num">04</div>
            <div class="test-tag">Consideration IV</div>
            <h3 class="test-title">The computers can do it now.</h3>
            <p class="test-body">
              Plaintiffs can run millions of race-neutral simulated maps and
              show the state&apos;s plan is an outlier. That tool didn&apos;t
              exist in 1986. Courts no longer need to take race-conscious
              redraws on faith &mdash; and the majority says they
              shouldn&apos;t.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ============================================================
         DISSENT
         ============================================================ -->
    <section class="section dissent">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="section-num" data-reveal>IV &middot; The dissent</div>
        <div class="dissent-grid">
          <div class="dissent-byline" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="1">
            <strong>Dissent &mdash; Kagan, J.</strong>
            joined by Sotomayor &amp; Jackson<br />
            Slip op., at 1
          </div>
          <blockquote class="dissent-quote" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="2">
            The consequences are likely to be far-reaching and grave.
            Today&apos;s decision renders Section 2 <em
              >all but a dead letter</em
            >.
          </blockquote>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ============================================================
         2A ANGLE
         ============================================================ -->
    <section class="section angle">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="angle-stamp" data-reveal>The 2A angle</div>
        <h2 class="section-title" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="1">
          A redistricting case is also a <em>gun rights case.</em>
        </h2>
        <p class="section-lede" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="2">
          The Fourteenth Amendment doesn&apos;t come in flavors. The same Equal
          Protection muscle the Court just flexed against race-based map drawing
          is the muscle that has to flex when state legislatures write gun laws
          that target some Americans and not others.
        </p>

        <div class="angle-grid">
          <div class="angle-body" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="3">
            <p>
              The colorblind Constitution isn&apos;t a slogan. It&apos;s a rule
              the government has to live by, and it&apos;s the rule the
              <em>Bruen</em>-era Second Amendment leans on every time a
              prohibited-person statute or a may-issue regime gets dragged into
              court.
            </p>
            <p>
              <strong>The history is ugly.</strong> Slave codes, Black Codes, the
              Mulford Act &mdash; American gun control was built, more than once,
              as a tool of racial control. Courts have spent the last decade dragging
              that history into the light because <em>Bruen</em> made history dispositive.
            </p>
            <p>
              <strong>What Callais reinforces:</strong> when the government makes
              a decision that turns on race &mdash; whether the decision is which
              neighborhoods share a congressman or which citizens get a permit &mdash;
              the Equal Protection Clause forces strict scrutiny and a colorblind
              alternative.
            </p>
            <p>
              That principle cuts every direction. It strikes down a gerrymander
              that packed Black voters. It would strike down a gun-permitting
              scheme that disqualifies Black applicants by proxy. And it pulls a
              thread that runs straight back to
              <em>Heller</em>, <em>Bruen</em>, and the &quot;text, history, and
              tradition&quot; test that gun owners now rely on as our floor.
            </p>

            <div class="angle-pull">
              The same Fourteenth Amendment that protects a redistricting
              plaintiff protects <span>a gun owner.</span>
            </div>

            <p>
              Read <em>Callais</em> as a doctrine memo, not a redistricting memo.
              The Court is reaffirming, in stark terms, that government acts based
              on race trigger the highest possible scrutiny &mdash; and that legislatures
              don&apos;t get to wave away that scrutiny by claiming a remedial purpose.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div data-reveal data-reveal-delay="4">
            <div class="precedent-stack">
              <div class="precedent">
                <div class="precedent-cite">McDonald v. City of Chicago</div>
                <div class="precedent-year">2010</div>
                <div class="precedent-line">
                  Incorporated the Second Amendment against the states through
                  the Fourteenth. Same amendment Callais is fought over.
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="precedent">
                <div class="precedent-cite">
                  Students for Fair Admissions v. Harvard
                </div>
                <div class="precedent-year">2023</div>
                <div class="precedent-line">
                  Killed race-conscious admissions. Same colorblind
                  Constitution; same Equal Protection clause; same six justices.
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="precedent">
                <div class="precedent-cite">
                  N.Y. State Rifle &amp; Pistol Ass&apos;n v. Bruen
                </div>
                <div class="precedent-year">2022</div>
                <div class="precedent-line">
                  Set the &quot;text, history, and tradition&quot; test for gun
                  laws &mdash; the test that is now exposing the racial history
                  of American firearm regulation.
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="precedent">
                <div class="precedent-cite">Rucho v. Common Cause</div>
                <div class="precedent-year">2019</div>
                <div class="precedent-line">
                  Held partisan gerrymandering claims aren&apos;t justiciable in
                  federal court. Callais closes the racial end-run around Rucho.
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="precedent">
                <div class="precedent-cite">District of Columbia v. Heller</div>
                <div class="precedent-year">2008</div>
                <div class="precedent-line">
                  Recognized the individual right to keep and bear arms.
                  Anchored in the same individual-rights framework that Callais
                  reinforces.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

